Argo CD is a pull based tool

arcgo cd have a controller in a cluster and pull the latestchanges from the repository and deploy it in the cluster.


argocd -> code in the repo(target state) -> kubernetes luster to be deployed(live state)

when synced it becomes in synced -> no difference.


when we change a target state the live state becomes outofsync -> there is a difference
(then argo pulls the change and then it becomes the synced)


kubernetes maaintains the repository service to store the cache of our local repo, then applcation  controller is used who compare the chaches from the repository service for any target and ive state difference.


Application in argocd:

group of manifests which make up an application, which is also an CRD in kubernetes



